cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Quiche Network Performance Measurement Experiment – RAPLA Node Configuration
abstract: This dataset contains the outputs from an experiment designed to measure
  network performance characteristics using the Quiche framework. The methodology
  involved configuring three nodes—rapla, tapa, and valga—with specific network topologies
  utilizing Time-Based Flow (TBF) queuing, Network Emulation (NETEM), and Quality
  of Service (QoS) parameters. Data transfer was synchronized via SSH key configuration
  and looped scripts to establish client, server, and proxy environments. The experiment
  generated random byte sequences for data volume testing and captured latency metrics
  during network traffic simulation. Associated artifacts include environment setup
  scripts, dependency installation commands, and result upload procedures.
